A communique was released by the school on 17 June, alerting parents of the infection, appealing that all Grade 7 and 12 learners to stay at home. Media Spokesperson for the Department of Education, Mr Jasper Zwane, confirmed that they had been informed of the infection and in turn, alerted the Department of Health. The school was advised on the course of action that needs to be taken before learners will be allowed to return to the institution.